HEADWORD: kalantas
<hw>kalantas</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A Philippine timber tree
(<spn>Toona calantas</spn> or <spn>Cedrela calantas</spn>) having hard
red fragrant wood.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Philippine mahogany, Philippine cedar, <spn>Toona
calantas</spn>, <spn>Cedrela calantas</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

